{"title_page": "Julia Haart", "text_new": "{{Infobox fashion designer\n| name               = \n| image              = Julia Haart.jpg\n| caption            = Julia Haart in 2019\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1971|4|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Moscow]], Russia\n| alma_mater         = \n| years_active       = \n| label_name         = {{flatlist|\n*[[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]]\n*[[Elite Model Management|Elite World]]}}\n*[http://e1972.com e1972]}}\n\n'''Julia Haart''' (born 1971 as '''Yulia Leibov''') is an American [[Fashion design|fashion designer]] and [[entrepreneur]]. Haart is the [[Chief Executive Officer]] and [[Chief Creative Officer]] of Elite World Group and the Chief Creative Officer e1972.\n\nIn 2013, Haart launched her namesake shoe collection, which ended when she joined [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]] in 2016.<ref>http://www.vogue.com/article/la-perla-julia-haart-creative-director/amp</ref> She joined the Italian luxury house as [[Creative Director]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/la-perla-announces-new-creative-director/|title=La Perla Announces New Creative Director|date=|publisher=vogue.co.uk|accessdate=2016-08-25}}</ref> In 2019, she was appointed [[Chief Executive Officer]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] Group, the world's largest network of model management agencies.<ref name=\"wwd.com2\">https://wwd.com/business-news/media/julia-haart-appointed-ceo-of-elite-world-1203089986/</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nYulia Leibov was born in [[Moscow]] in 1971.\u00a0 At age 3, Leibov and her immediate family immigrated to [[Rome]], then to [[Vienna]], before settling in [[Austin, Texas]] at age five. Leibov's parents were strict followers of the Heimishe [[Yeshivish|yeshivishe]] sect of Ultra-[[Orthodox Judaism]]. At age 11 Leibov and her family moved to the insular [[Hasidic Judaism|Chasidic]] community in [[Monsey, New York]]. Leibov attended Bais Yakkov Girls school. After graduating Leibov became a teacher of [[Haredi Judaism|ultra orthodox]] Jewish philosophy. After leaving the community in 2013, Haart founded her shoe company, Julia Haart. In 2016, she joined [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]] as Creative Director. In 2019, she became [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] and [[Chief Creative Officer|CCO]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]].<ref name=\"wwd.com3\" /> She currently lives in New York with her husband [[Silvio Scaglia]].\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Julia Haart the brand ===\nIn 2013, Haart launched her shoe collection, creating a high heeled shoe that evenly distributes pressure across the entire foot. To do this, she partnered with an Italian ski boot engineer and a German<ref>{{cite web |title=Advice For Women Working In Male-Dominated Industries From La Perla's Julia Haart |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lisaroepe/2017/04/28/advice-for-women-working-in-male-dominated-industries-from-la-perlas-julia-haart/#7e8a5ddc2b2a |website=Forbes}}</ref> company that creates a gel used to insulate the NASA space station.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lisaroepe/2017/04/28/advice-for-women-working-in-male-dominated-industries-from-la-perlas-julia-haart/#1acac0fe2b2a/|title= Julia Haart Giving Advice to Women Working in Male Dominated Industries |publisher=forbes.com |date= |accessdate=2017-04-28}}</ref>\n\nHaart had two global patents pending relating to the comfort and wearability of her shoe design.\n\n=== La Perla ===\nFollowing her appointment as Creative Director of [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]], Haart launched<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farra |first1=Emily |title=Pre-Fall 2018 |url=https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/pre-fall-2018/la-perla |website=Vogue}}</ref> a new approach to ready-to-wear<ref>{{cite web |title=La Perla Has a New Creative Director and a Surprising New Approach to Ready-to-Wear |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/la-perla-julia-haart-creative-director |website=Vogue}}</ref> for the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.drapersonline.com/product-and-trade-shows/la-perlas-wisdom-creative-director-julia-haarts-mission-of-transformation/7028944.article/|title= La Perla's wisdom: Creative director Julia Haart's mission of transformation |publisher=drapersonline.com |date= |accessdate=2018-02-13}}</ref> At [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]], Haart created the first stretch Leavers Lace, and launched a collection of ready-to-wear<ref>{{cite web |title=What's New In Lingerie |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/a20005/whats-new-in-lingerie/ |website=Harpers Bazaar}}</ref> with built-in support. Pieces were sold both in dress size and bra size. Her aim was to create a unique<ref>{{cite web |title=Four questions to Julia Haart, new creative director of La Perla |url=https://www.vogue.fr/fashion/fashion-news/articles/4-questions-to-julia-haart-new-creative-director-of-la-perla/45528 |website=Vogue}}</ref> fusion of lingerie and fashion.<ref>{{cite web |title=Glamorous daywear that channels luxe lingerie |url=https://howtospendit.ft.com/womens-style/202348-glamorous-daywear-that-channels-luxe-lingerie |accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nFor her Fall/Winter 2017 fashion show, Haart<ref>{{cite web |title=Beyond the bedroom: why La Perla creative director Julia Haart heralds a new direction for lingerie brand |url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/fashion-luxury/article/2067853/beyond-bedroom-why-la-perla-creative-director-julia-haart |website=South China Morning Post}}</ref> constructed a \u201cLa Perla Manor\u201d runway show, where [[Naomi Campbell]]<ref>{{cite web |title=New York Fashion Week Fall/Winter 2017: Naomi Campbell And Kendall Jenner Walk In La Perla |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/10/new-york-fashion-week-fall-winter-ready-to-wear-2017-la-perla-kendall-jenner-naomi-campbell/#6ef7509f7c95 |website=Forbes}}</ref>, [[Lindsey Wixson]], [[Sasha Pivovarova]] and [[Kendall Jenner]] walked.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observer.com/2017/03/julia-haart-is-making-la-perla-about-more-than-just-sexy-lingerie/|title= Julia Haart Is Making La Perla About More Than Just Sexy Lingerie |publisher=observer.com |date= |accessdate=2017-03-15}}</ref>\n\nHaart is known for her 2017 [[Met Gala]] dress designed for [[Kendall Jenner]]<ref>{{cite web |title=How I Get It Done: Julia Haart, Creative Director at La Perla |url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/05/julia-haart-la-perla-creative-director-daily-routine.htmlkend |website=The Cut}}</ref>. The gown consisted of 85,000 Crystals affixed to a single string<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.elle.com/fashion/celebrity-style/news/a44952/kendall-jenner-naked-dress/|title= Kendall Jenner Wore 85,000 Crystals Held Together By a Piece of String to the Met Gala |publisher=elle.com |date= |accessdate=2017-05-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Elite World Group ===\n\nIn 2019, Haart was appointed [[Chief Executive Officer]] and [[Chief Creative Officer]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]]. [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] represents more than 3500 models with global brands including [[Elite Model Management]], [[Women Management|Women Model Management]], [[The Society Management|The Society Model Management]], [https://www.suprememanagement.com/home.web Supreme], 360, Stage, and the Creatives. [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] top talent in the network include [[Kendall Jenner]], [[Rita Ora]], [[Adriana Lima]], [[Irina Shayk]], [[Behati Prinsloo]], [[Josephine Skriver]], [[Izabel Goulart]], [[Liu Wen (model)|Liu Wen]], [[Willow Smith]], [[Jasmine Sanders]], and [[Jourdan Dunn]]. \n\nJulia Haart\u2019s goal is to help Elite\u2019s talent network build more stable careers while leveraging their social media followings to reinforce the agency\u2019s business.\n\nTwo new divisions will launch brands, produce in-house digital content and provide influencer marketing services.\n\nBy providing user-friendly access to talent it has trained, Elite is hoping it will be preferred by clients over the growing number of new influencer marketing agencies. \"Traditionally, models had no way to grow their own career,\" says Haart, adding that many were phased out of the industry once they outgrew the runway. \u201cNow, I have the unique opportunity to help my talent and shift the power dynamic.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |last1=Annachiara |first1=Biondi |title=Elite World Group is tapping modelling talent to build a media company |url=https://www.voguebusiness.com/companies/elite-ceo-julia-haart-interview |website=Vogue Business |publisher=Conde Nast |accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== e1972 ===\nUnder Haart, [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] launched its first global fashion brand titled e1972.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://wwd.com/fashion-news/designer-luxury/elite-world-to-launch-fashion-brand-1203032948/|title= Elite World to Launch Fashion Brand |publisher=wwd.com |date= |accessdate=2019-02-19}}</ref> Haart launched the [http://e1972.com e1972]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bottoni |first1=Valentina|title=Inclusiva, sostenibile e sizeless: la moda secondo e1972 |url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/elite-nuovo-brand-moda-e1972-julia |website=vogue.it |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>  Autumn/Fall collection during NYFW February 2020; the 62-look show was opened by Adut Akech, who is signed to Elite Models. The evening featured a performance from singer-songwriter Bebe Rexha of her hit single, Meant to Be. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Browchuk |first1=Elisee |title=No Size Fits All, Elite World\u2019s Julia Haart Debuts e1972 on The Runway |url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/e1972-spring2020-nyfw?fbclid=IwAR3B0MV2sSiO-JFypkSw4Sdp8Sl6DUAjZLSMZbWtGPcxlL7BhQ9sc-Tn9a8 |website=Vogue |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n== External links ==\n\n*{{fashiondesigner|id=julia-haart}}\n\n*{{IMDb name|nm9788273|Julia Haart|section=bio}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox fashion designer\n| name               = \n| image              = Julia Haart.jpg\n| caption            = Julia Haart in 2019\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1971|4|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Moscow]], Russia\n| alma_mater         = \n| years_active       = \n| label_name         = {{flatlist|\n*[[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]]\n*[[Elite Model Management|Elite World]]}}\n*[http://e1972.com e1972]}}\n\n\n'''Julia Haart''' (born 1971 as '''Yulia Leibov''') is an American [[fashion design]]er and [[entrepreneur]]. Haart is the [[Chief Executive Officer]] and [[Chief Creative Officer]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] and the [[Chief Creative Officer]] of e1972.\n\nShe is married to the Italian billionaire [[Silvio Scaglia]] owner of model agency [[Elite Model Management|\u00c9lite World]] and luxury company  [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]]\n\nIn 2013, Haart launched her namesake shoe collection, which ended when she joined [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]] in 2016.<ref>http://www.vogue.com/article/la-perla-julia-haart-creative-director/amp</ref> She joined the Italian luxury house as [[Creative Director]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/la-perla-announces-new-creative-director/|title= La Perla Announces New Creative Director |publisher=vogue.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-08-25}}</ref> In 2019, she was appointed [[Chief Executive Officer]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]], the world's largest network of model management agencies.<ref name=\"wwd.com\">https://wwd.com/business-news/media/julia-haart-appointed-ceo-of-elite-world-1203089986/</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nYulia Leibov was born in [[Moscow]] in 1971.  At age 3, Leibov and her immediate family immigrated to [[Rome]], then to [[Vienna]], before settling in [[Austin, Texas]] at age five. Leibov's parents were strict followers of the Heimishe [[yeshivish]]e sect of Ultra-[[Orthodox Judaism]]. At age 11 Leibov and her family moved to the insular [[Hasidic Judaism|Chasidic]] community in [[Monsey, New York]]. Leibov attended Bais Yakkov Girls school. After graduating Leibov became a teacher of [[Haredi Judaism|ultra orthodox]] Jewish philosophy. After leaving the community in 2013, Haart founded her shoe company, Julia Haart. In 2016, after selling her shoe company to la Perla and screwing her partners {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}, she joined [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]] as Creative Director. In 2019, she became [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] and [[Chief Creative Officer|CCO]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]].<ref name=\"wwd.com\" /> She currently lives in New York with her husband [[Silvio Scaglia]].\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Julia Haart the brand ===\nIn 2013, Haart launched her shoe collection, creating a high heeled shoe that evenly distributes pressure across the entire foot. To do this, she partnered with an Italian ski boot engineer and a German<ref>{{cite web |title=Advice For Women Working In Male-Dominated Industries From La Perla's Julia Haart |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lisaroepe/2017/04/28/advice-for-women-working-in-male-dominated-industries-from-la-perlas-julia-haart/#7e8a5ddc2b2a |website=Forbes}}</ref> company that creates a gel used to insulate the NASA space station.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lisaroepe/2017/04/28/advice-for-women-working-in-male-dominated-industries-from-la-perlas-julia-haart/#1acac0fe2b2a/|title= Julia Haart Giving Advice to Women Working in Male Dominated Industries |publisher=forbes.com |date= |accessdate=2017-04-28}}</ref>\n\nHaart had two global patents pending relating to the comfort and wearability of her shoe design.\n\n=== La Perla ===\nFollowing her appointment as Creative Director of [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]], Haart launched<ref>{{cite web |last1=Farra |first1=Emily |title=Pre-Fall 2018 |url=https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/pre-fall-2018/la-perla |website=Vogue}}</ref> a new approach to ready-to-wear<ref>{{cite web |title=La Perla Has a New Creative Director and a Surprising New Approach to Ready-to-Wear |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/la-perla-julia-haart-creative-director |website=Vogue}}</ref> for the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.drapersonline.com/product-and-trade-shows/la-perlas-wisdom-creative-director-julia-haarts-mission-of-transformation/7028944.article/|title= La Perla's wisdom: Creative director Julia Haart's mission of transformation |publisher=drapersonline.com |date= |accessdate=2018-02-13}}</ref> At [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]], Haart created the first stretch Leavers Lace, and launched a collection of ready-to-wear<ref>{{cite web |title=What's New In Lingerie |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/a20005/whats-new-in-lingerie/ |website=Harpers Bazaar}}</ref> with built-in support. Pieces were sold both in dress size and bra size. Her aim was to create a unique<ref>{{cite web |title=Four questions to Julia Haart, new creative director of La Perla |url=https://www.vogue.fr/fashion/fashion-news/articles/4-questions-to-julia-haart-new-creative-director-of-la-perla/45528 |website=Vogue}}</ref> fusion of lingerie and fashion.<ref>{{cite web |title=Glamorous daywear that channels luxe lingerie |url=https://howtospendit.ft.com/womens-style/202348-glamorous-daywear-that-channels-luxe-lingerie |accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nFor her Fall/Winter 2017 fashion show, Haart<ref>{{cite web |title=Beyond the bedroom: why La Perla creative director Julia Haart heralds a new direction for lingerie brand |url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/fashion-luxury/article/2067853/beyond-bedroom-why-la-perla-creative-director-julia-haart |website=South China Morning Post}}</ref> constructed a \u201cLa Perla Manor\u201d runway show, where [[Naomi Campbell]]<ref>{{cite web |title=New York Fashion Week Fall/Winter 2017: Naomi Campbell And Kendall Jenner Walk In La Perla |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/10/new-york-fashion-week-fall-winter-ready-to-wear-2017-la-perla-kendall-jenner-naomi-campbell/#6ef7509f7c95 |website=Forbes}}</ref>, [[Lindsey Wixson]], [[Sasha Pivovarova]] and [[Kendall Jenner]] walked.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observer.com/2017/03/julia-haart-is-making-la-perla-about-more-than-just-sexy-lingerie/|title= Julia Haart Is Making La Perla About More Than Just Sexy Lingerie |publisher=observer.com |date= |accessdate=2017-03-15}}</ref>\n\nHaart is known for her 2017 [[Met Gala]] dress designed for [[Kendall Jenner]]<ref>{{cite web |title=How I Get It Done: Julia Haart, Creative Director at La Perla |url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/05/julia-haart-la-perla-creative-director-daily-routine.htmlkend |website=The Cut}}</ref>. The gown consisted of 85,000 Crystals affixed to a single string<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.elle.com/fashion/celebrity-style/news/a44952/kendall-jenner-naked-dress/|title= Kendall Jenner Wore 85,000 Crystals Held Together By a Piece of String to the Met Gala |publisher=elle.com |date= |accessdate=2017-05-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Elite World Group ===\n\nIn 2019, Haart was appointed [[Chief Executive Officer]] and [[Chief Creative Officer]] of [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]]. [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] represents more than 3500 models with global brands including [[Elite Model Management]], [[Women Management|Women Model Management]], [[The Society Management|The Society Model Management]], [https://www.suprememanagement.com/home.web Supreme], 360, Stage, and the Creatives. [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] top talent in the network include [[Kendall Jenner]], [[Rita Ora]], [[Adriana Lima]], [[Irina Shayk]], [[Behati Prinsloo]], [[Josephine Skriver]], [[Izabel Goulart]], [[Liu Wen (model)|Liu Wen]], [[Willow Smith]], [[Jasmine Sanders]], and [[Jourdan Dunn]]. \n\nJulia Haart\u2019s goal is to help Elite\u2019s talent network build more stable careers while leveraging their social media followings to reinforce the agency\u2019s business.\n\nTwo new divisions will launch brands, produce in-house digital content and provide influencer marketing services.\n\nBy providing user-friendly access to talent it has trained, Elite is hoping it will be preferred by clients over the growing number of new influencer marketing agencies. \"Traditionally, models had no way to grow their own career,\" says Haart, adding that many were phased out of the industry once they outgrew the runway. \u201cNow, I have the unique opportunity to help my talent and shift the power dynamic.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |last1=Annachiara |first1=Biondi |title=Elite World Group is tapping modelling talent to build a media company |url=https://www.voguebusiness.com/companies/elite-ceo-julia-haart-interview |website=Vogue Business |publisher=Conde Nast |accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== e1972 ===\nUnder Haart, [[Elite Model Management|Elite World]] launched its first global fashion brand titled e1972.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://wwd.com/fashion-news/designer-luxury/elite-world-to-launch-fashion-brand-1203032948/|title= Elite World to Launch Fashion Brand |publisher=wwd.com |date= |accessdate=2019-02-19}}</ref> Haart launched the [http://e1972.com e1972]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bottoni |first1=Valentina|title=Inclusiva, sostenibile e sizeless: la moda secondo e1972 |url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/elite-nuovo-brand-moda-e1972-julia |website=vogue.it |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref>  Autumn/Fall collection during NYFW February 2020; the 62-look show was opened by Adut Akech, who is signed to Elite Models. The evening featured a performance from singer-songwriter Bebe Rexha of her hit single, Meant to Be. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Browchuk |first1=Elisee |title=No Size Fits All, Elite World\u2019s Julia Haart Debuts e1972 on The Runway |url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/e1972-spring2020-nyfw?fbclid=IwAR3B0MV2sSiO-JFypkSw4Sdp8Sl6DUAjZLSMZbWtGPcxlL7BhQ9sc-Tn9a8 |website=Vogue |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}